EXECUTION EXAMPLE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Agent Execution Trace:

  agent.state = Idle

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Planning
     (Goal: "Answer user question")
     (Create tasks: [SearchInfo, AnalyzeData, GenerateResponse])

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Executing
     (Execute Task[0]: SearchInfo)
     (Tool: web_search("What is AI?"))
     (Result: "AI is...")

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Observing
     (Collect result)
     (Store to memory["search_result"])
     (Validate: ✓ Valid)

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Executing
     (Execute Task[1]: AnalyzeData)
     (Tool: analyze_text(memory["search_result"]))
     (Result: {"topics": ["AI", "ML", ...]})

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Observing
     (Collect result)
     (Store to memory["analysis"])

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Executing
     (Execute Task[2]: GenerateResponse)
     (Tool: llm_response(memory["analysis"]))
     (Result: "AI is artificial intelligence...")

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Observing
     (All tasks done!)
     (All success!)

  agent.next_state()
  → state = Completed
     (Goal achieved ✓)


